## Configuration Guidelines

### Interface ID Ranges
Assign unique interface ID ranges to each panel to avoid conflicts:

- **Template Panel**: 29000-29099
- **Inventory Panel**: 30000-30099
- **Skills Panel**: 31000-31099
- **Combat Panel**: 32000-32199
- **Quest Panel**: 33000-33099
- **Settings Panel**: 34000-34099

### Config File Structure
```java
public class YourPanelConfig {
    // Interface IDs (use unique range)
    public static final int PANEL_ACTIVATION_ID = 30000;
    public static final int PRIMARY_ACTION_ID = 30001;

    // Display settings
    public static final int MAX_ITEMS = 50;
    public static final int GRID_COLUMNS = 4;

    // Feature flags
    public static final boolean ENABLE_ANIMATIONS = true;
    public static final boolean ENABLE_TOOLTIPS = true;

    // Resource paths
    public static final String SPRITE_PATH = "sprites/yourpanel/";
}
```

## Button Creation Examples

### Using InteractiveButtonUtil (Recommended)
```java
// Standard buttons with automatic rainbow hover
JButton refreshBtn = InteractiveButtonUtil.addInteractiveButton("Refresh", YourPanelConfig.REFRESH_ID);
JButton actionBtn = InteractiveButtonUtil.addInteractiveButton("Action", YourPanelConfig.ACTION_ID);

// Sprite buttons
JButton skillBtn = InteractiveButtonUtil.addSpriteButton("sprites/skills/magic.png", YourPanelConfig.SKILL_ID);

// Combined text + sprite
JButton comboBtn = InteractiveButtonUtil.addInteractiveButton("Cast Spell", "sprites/spells/fireball.png", YourPanelConfig.SPELL_ID);
```

### Using Custom Styling
```java
// Custom styled buttons using YourPanelStyle
JButton primaryBtn = YourPanelStyle.createPrimaryButton("Primary Action", YourPanelConfig.PRIMARY_ID);
JButton dangerBtn = YourPanelStyle.createDangerButton("Delete", YourPanelConfig.DELETE_ID);
JButton successBtn = YourPanelStyle.createSuccessButton("Confirm", YourPanelConfig.CONFIRM_ID);
```

## Panel Registration

### 1. Register in UIDockFrame
```java
// In UIDockFrame.java initialization
registerPanel(new YourPanelPanel());
```

### 2. Add to DockPanelMapping (if using RSInterfaces)
```java
// In DockPanelMapping.java
YOUR_PANEL(30000, 30001, "Your Panel Name", YourPanelPanel.class),
```

## Best Practices

### File Organization
- Keep each file focused on its specific purpose
- Use meaningful method names that describe the action
- Group related constants together in config files
- Create reusable style methods for common components

### Interface ID Management
- Use sequential IDs within your assigned range
- Document what each ID does in comments
- Group related IDs together (e.g., 30000-30009 for main actions, 30010-30019 for settings)

### Color and Styling
- Extend the base ColorConfig colors rather than hardcoding
- Create theme-aware styling methods
- Use consistent spacing and sizing across your panel
- Make use of the rainbow hover system

### Error Handling
- Always check `Client.loggedIn` before server operations
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors appropriately for debugging
- Handle edge cases gracefully

